All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
ConsoleReader
The ConsoleReader class provides utility methods for reading different types of input from the console.
ContactImpl
The ContactImpl class represents a contact with various details such as street, city, state, zip code, country, and phone number.
Demo
The Demo class is the entry point of the program and invokes the menuPrincipal method.
EditionImpl
The EditionImpl class represents an implementation of the Edition interface and provides functionality to manage a CBL edition.
EditionJsonSerializer
The EditionJsonSerializer class is responsible for serializing and deserializing ManageEditions objects to/from a file.
FacilitatorImpl
The FacilitatorImpl class represents a facilitator participant in a project.
InstituitionImpl
The InstituitionImpl class represents an institution.
ListNumberOfParticipantsPerEdition
The ListNumberOfParticipantsPerEdition class provides a method for generating a string representation of the number of participants per edition in a ManageEditions object.
ListTasksNoSubmission
The ListTasksNoSubmission class provides a method for generating a string representation of tasks within a project that have no submissions.
ManageEditions
The ManageTasks class provides methods for managing tasks information.
ManageParticipants
The ManageParticipants class provides methods for managing participant information.
ManageSubmissions
The ManageSubmissions class provides methods for managing submissions information.
ManageTasks
The ManageTasks class provides methods for managing tasks information.
ManageTemplates
The ManageTasks class provides a method for getting the project_template information.
Menus
The `Menus` class represents the menu system for the project management application.
ParticipantImpl
ParticipantImpl is a class that represents a participant in a project.
PartnerImpl
PartnerImpl is a class that represents a partner in a project.
ProjectImpl
The `ProjectImpl` class represents a project implementation in a project management system.
ProjectJsonSerializer
The ProjectJsonSerializer class is responsible for reading project data from a JSON template and creating a ProjectImpl object based on the data.
StudentImpl
The StudentImpl class represents a student participant in a project.
SubmissionImpl
This class represents an implementation of the Submission interface.
TaskImpl
The TaskImpl class represents a task implementation with a title, description, start date, and duration.
TotalOfTasksCalculator
The TotalOfTasksCalculator class provides methods for calculating the total number of tasks in a collection of editions.
